Drain any excess liquid from @chicken cutlets{20%ounce}; place in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium low and simmer until chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}; discard cooking liquid. When cool enough to handle, shred chicken with two #forks{}. (You can also cut it into cubes!)

While chicken cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and dice @carrots{9%ounce} into ¼-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(peeled and diced) into ¼-inch pieces. Drop @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} (in packets) into a small #bowl{} of warm water to soften.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a medium pot over medium-high heat. Add carrots and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit}, 2¼ cups water (4½ cups for 8 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, mix cream cheese, @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the @cheddar cheese{1%cup}, and ¼ cup water (½ cup for 8 servings).

When rice is done cooking, fluff with a #fork{}.

Transfer shredded chicken and rice to bowl with cream cheese mixture; add @peas{4%ounce} and stir to evenly coat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Adjust rack to top position; heat broiler to high.

Transfer filling to an 8-by-8-inch #baking dish{} (9-by-13-inch baking dish for 8 servings).

Sprinkle evenly with remaining cheddar, then top with @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}. Broil until cheese melts and panko is lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to prevent burning!

Let casserole rest for ~{5%minutes}. Divide between plates and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.